{"id":"1802.10169","submitter":"Reza Moulavi Ardakani","authors":"Reza Moulavi Ardakani","title":"Time Reversal Invariance in Quantum Mechanics","comments":"Master's Thesis, 67 pages, http://hdl.handle.net/2346/73464","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"physics.hist-ph quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Symmetries have a crucial role in today's physics. In this thesis, we are\nmostly concerned with time reversal invariance (T-symmetry). A physical system\nis time reversal invariant if its underlying laws are not sensitive to the\ndirection of time. There are various accounts of time reversal transformation\nresulting in different views on whether or not a given theory in physics is\ntime reversal invariant. With a focus on quantum mechanics, I describe the\nstandard account of time reversal and compare it with my alternative account,\narguing why it deserves serious attention. Then, I review three known ways to\nT-violation in quantum mechanics, and explain two unique experiments made to\ndetect it in the neutral K and B mesons.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 16 Feb 2018 00:22:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-03-01"}
